---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work with me | Research activation and narrative strategy"
  description="I help organisations implement Editorial Intelligence — building the narrative systems, evidence workflows and editorial capability that turn distributed knowledge into a compounding strategic asset."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="work-inner">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">Work with me</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">You have the research.<br />I'll find the argument.</h1>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>I help B2B organisations turn scattered research, customer insight and market evidence into distinctive positions that strengthen thought leadership, give content direction and make existing insight work harder.</p>
          <p>Most organisations already have more insight than they realise: research reports, customer stories, webinars and events, advisory board discussions, sales feedback and market analysis.</p>
          <p>The problem is not the absence of evidence. It is that the evidence is scattered, underused and rarely connected into a sustained argument.</p>
          <p>A report gets published. A webinar is broadcast. An event produces useful conversations. Then the next campaign starts and the learning disappears into another folder, deck or Teams thread.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence builds the missing narrative layer: determining what the evidence means, what the organisation can credibly claim and how that knowledge can compound over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="work-btn">Discuss what you already have</a>
          <a href="#services" class="work-link">Explore the services ↓</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Credibility strip -->
      <div class="credibility-strip mb-16">
        <p class="credibility-line">Developed through two decades of editorial work in complex B2B markets — including research activation, customer evidence, webinar and event intelligence and thought leadership development.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Problem recognition -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-6">This work is useful when</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-6">Typically, I work with content, thought leadership, brand, research and communications leaders who are responsible for turning organisational expertise into market authority.</p>
        <ul class="work-list mb-6">
          <li>You commissioned valuable research, but it produced little beyond the original report</li>
          <li>You have customer insight but no coherent strategic narrative connecting it</li>
          <li>Your thought leadership consists of individual assets rather than a recognisable position</li>
          <li>You run webinars and events that generate valuable discussion, but the insight rarely travels beyond the original session</li>
          <li>Your content programme resets with every campaign instead of accumulating authority</li>
          <li>You are preparing to invest in more content but suspect that volume is not the real problem</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note">The right engagement depends on how clearly you already understand the problem.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Services -->
      <section id="services" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">Ways to work together</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-12">
          <p>Some organisations need to understand what they already have. Others have a particular body of research, a thought leadership opportunity or a stream of webinar and event insight ready to develop.</p>
          <p>The services below provide different entry points into the same underlying work: connecting evidence, finding the argument and building a system around it.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Flagship: Narrative audit -->
        <div class="service-flagship mb-12">
          <p class="service-eyebrow">Start here</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading">Narrative audit</h3>
          <p class="service-prop">Find out what your existing evidence actually adds up to.</p>
          <div class="prose-section mb-6">
            <p>A structured review of your research, content, customer insight and market evidence. I identify the strongest argument already present, assess what genuinely supports it and show where valuable signals are being missed.</p>
            <p>The audit is designed for organisations that know they are sitting on useful material but do not yet have a clear view of the narrative opportunity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-includes mb-6">
            <p class="service-includes-label">Includes</p>
            <ul class="work-list">
              <li>The strongest through-lines across your existing material</li>
              <li>The evidence with the greatest strategic value</li>
              <li>Gaps, contradictions and overlooked signals</li>
              <li>Existing assets worth reactivating</li>
              <li>The narrative territories you could credibly own</li>
              <li>Recommended priorities for further development</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="what-you-leave mb-6">
            <p class="what-you-leave-label">What you leave with</p>
            <p class="what-you-leave-desc">A clear view of the strongest argument already present in your material, the evidence that supports it, the gaps that weaken it and the narrative opportunities worth developing.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a concise narrative audit, evidence map and opportunity brief. Fixed scope and fixed fee. Typically completed within two to three weeks.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="work-btn mt-6 inline-flex">Discuss a narrative audit</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Build layer -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-8">Build from the evidence</p>
          <div class="service-dev-grid">

            <!-- Research activation -->
            <div class="service-dev-card">
              <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Research activation</h3>
              <p class="service-prop-sm">Your research should produce more than a report.</p>
              <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
                <p>For organisations that have commissioned original research and need it to work harder.</p>
                <p>I turn the findings into a clear strategic argument, determine which evidence matters most and design a structure through which the research can support thought leadership, editorial content, executive communications, webinars, events and future research.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="what-you-leave mb-4">
                <p class="what-you-leave-label">What you leave with</p>
                <p class="what-you-leave-desc-sm">A clear research narrative, an evidence hierarchy and a practical activation system for thought leadership, executive communications, webinars, events and future content.</p>
              </div>
              <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a research narrative and activation system.</p>
              <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="service-inline-link">See how this works through Hidden Hours →</a>
            </div>

            <!-- Thought leadership architecture -->
            <div class="service-dev-card">
              <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Thought leadership architecture</h3>
              <p class="service-prop-sm">Turn organisational expertise into a position the market can recognise.</p>
              <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
                <p>For organisations with credible expertise, evidence and opinions but no coherent market position connecting them.</p>
                <p>I bring together research, customer experience, executive expertise and market signals to define the problem the organisation can own, its distinctive interpretation and the evidence required to sustain it.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="what-you-leave mb-4">
                <p class="what-you-leave-label">What you leave with</p>
                <p class="what-you-leave-desc-sm">A distinctive strategic position, the evidence and proprietary ideas that support it, and an editorial architecture through which the organisation can develop it consistently.</p>
              </div>
              <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a thought leadership platform and editorial architecture.</p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Webinar and event intelligence -->
        <div class="service-specialist mb-12">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-6">A specialist application</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Webinar and event intelligence</h3>
          <p class="service-prop-sm">Make the value of a conversation last beyond the session itself.</p>
          <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
            <p>Webinars, roundtables, conferences, advisory boards and customer events generate valuable insight — speaker expertise, audience questions, recurring themes, areas of agreement and tension, poll findings, market signals — but much of it disappears into recordings, transcripts and follow-up content that is rarely revisited.</p>
            <p>I analyse the conversations to identify emerging themes, useful evidence, narrative implications and signals worth tracking. The work does not cover webinar production, promotion or event management.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-you-leave mb-4">
            <p class="what-you-leave-label">What you leave with</p>
            <p class="what-you-leave-desc-sm">A clear account of what the conversation revealed, an organised bank of evidence and quotations, and recommendations for applying the insight across thought leadership, content and future research.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome mb-3">Deliverable: a webinar or event intelligence report, evidence bank and activation plan.</p>
          <a href="/experiments/event-intelligence" class="service-inline-link">See the webinar and event intelligence approach →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Advisory -->
        <div class="service-advisory">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-6">Continue the work</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Editorial Intelligence advisory</h3>
          <p class="service-prop-sm">An ongoing editorial perspective on what your evidence means and where the narrative should go next.</p>
          <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
            <p>For teams that need continuing strategic judgement rather than another production retainer.</p>
            <p>The advisory relationship can include reviewing new research, connecting new evidence to existing narratives, challenging content plans, identifying emerging signals and deciding when the strategic argument needs to evolve.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-you-leave mb-4">
            <p class="what-you-leave-label">What you leave with</p>
            <p class="what-you-leave-desc-sm">Continuing senior editorial judgement on what new evidence means, how it connects to the existing position and where the narrative should develop next.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome mb-4">Retainer-based, with the scope defined around the organisation's needs.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="work-btn">Discuss ongoing advisory</a>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Proof -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">The practice behind the services</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-10">
          <p>This work is grounded in two decades of editorial and content experience in complex B2B markets: developing research-led narratives, turning customer insight into useful evidence and connecting organisational knowledge into systems that outlast individual campaigns.</p>
          <p>The work documented across this site shows the methodology in practice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-items">
          <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Hidden Hours — Sage</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How one research programme was extended beyond its original report into an ongoing narrative platform, editorial series, diagnostic concept and source of market intelligence.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Winning in Small — Sage</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How event insight, customer stories and survey evidence were synthesised into a clearer strategic argument.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/applications" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Applications</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How Editorial Intelligence can be applied across research, events, customer evidence, AI workflows and content activation.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Distinction -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-6">A small, senior practice</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>I am not an agency. I work on a small number of engagements at a time, which means the analysis, synthesis and strategic thinking are carried out by me rather than delegated through a larger team.</p>
          <p>The work is particularly suited to established B2B organisations, startups and scaleups in fintech, SaaS, professional services and other complex markets where credibility depends on connecting evidence with genuine subject expertise.</p>
          <p>For startups, Editorial Intelligence can also help build and test the initial position before a large body of evidence has accumulated. <a href="/applications/startups-scaleups" class="work-inline-link">Explore Editorial Intelligence for startups and scaleups →</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-6">Start with what you already have</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Tell me what research, insight or expertise you are sitting on. I'll help you determine whether there is a stronger argument inside it — and what it would take to develop it.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="contact-cta">
          asavin@editorialintelligence.co
          <span class="contact-cta-arrow">→</span>
        </a>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .work-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* ── Prose ── */
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-section-sm {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .prose-section-sm p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-note {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .prose-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  /* ── Credibility strip ── */
  .credibility-strip {
    border-left: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 40%, transparent);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 4%, transparent);
    border-radius: 0 3px 3px 0;
  }

  .credibility-line {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Lists ── */
  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .work-list-sm {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .work-list-sm li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list-sm li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Hero CTAs ── */
  .hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .work-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .work-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .work-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .work-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  /* ── Service labels ── */
  .service-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .service-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Flagship ── */
  .service-flagship {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .service-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .service-prop {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .service-includes { }

  .service-includes-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ── What you leave with ── */
  .what-you-leave {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-top: 0.875rem;
  }

  .what-you-leave-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .what-you-leave-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .what-you-leave-desc-sm {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Dev grid ── */
  .service-dev-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .service-dev-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .service-dev-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .service-heading-sm {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .service-prop-sm {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .service-inline-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    display: block;
    opacity: 0.8;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .service-inline-link:hover { opacity: 1; }

  /* ── Specialist ── */
  .service-specialist {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  /* ── Advisory ── */
  .service-advisory {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  /* ── Proof ── */
  .proof-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .proof-item {
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .proof-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .proof-item:hover { background: var(--color-surface-tertiary); }

  .proof-item-inner {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .proof-label {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .proof-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
  }

  .proof-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Outcome line ── */
  .engagement-outcome {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    display: block;
  }

  .mt-6 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .mb-3 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .mb-4 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  /* ── Contact ── */
  .contact-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-cta:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .work-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .work-inline-link:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .contact-cta-arrow { transition: transform 0.2s; }
  .contact-cta:hover .contact-cta-arrow { transform: translateX(3px); }
</style>
